AC   P18275;
Arginine/ornithine antiporter.
"The arc operon for anaerobic arginine catabolism in Pseudomonas
aeruginosa contains an additional gene, arcD, encoding a membrane
protein.";
"Complete genome sequence of Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1, an
opportunistic pathogen.";
"arcD, the first gene of the arc operon for anaerobic arginine
catabolism in Pseudomonas aeruginosa, encodes an arginine-ornithine
exchanger.";
-!- FUNCTION: Catalyzes an electroneutral exchange between arginine
    and ornithine to allow high-efficiency energy conversion in the
    arginine deiminase pathway.
-!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Cell inner membrane; multi-pass membrane
    protein (Potential).
-!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the amino acid-polyamine-organocation (APC)
    superfamily.
Amino-acid transport; Antiport; Complete proteome; Inner membrane;
